# StringBuilder

Since Strings are immutable, use `StringBuilder` for frequent modifications.

```java
StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder("Java");

sb.append(" Programming");

System.out.println(sb);
```

Output:

```
Java Programming
```

### Useful StringBuilder Methods

| Method      | Description        |
| ----------- | ------------------ |
| `append()`  | Adds text          |
| `insert()`  | Inserts text       |
| `delete()`  | Deletes characters |
| `reverse()` | Reverses string    |
| `replace()` | Replaces text      |

Example:

```java
StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder("Java");

sb.reverse();

System.out.println(sb);
```

Output:

```
avaJ
```

